# build-border-architecture (Hexa Design System)

Takes border-radius and border-width values in the **Hexa Design System** file â€” wherever they
currently live, however they're named â€” and folds them into Hexa's established 3-tier
architecture: both live under `2. Tokens > Border-Radius/[step]` and `2. Tokens > Border-Width/[step]`,
aliasing `1. Primitives > Scale` only, named with t-shirt sizing, identical across Hexa's 5 brand
modes unless explicitly told otherwise. Any legacy standalone collection (e.g. a stray `4. Radius`)
is deleted once migration is verified and no live bindings remain.

This is the Hexa-specific version of this workflow â€” it hardcodes Hexa's known structure rather
than rediscovering it each run, the same way `build-typography-architecture` does for type.

