## Standing naming & structure conventions

- **Tier 2 location only.** `Border-Radius/` and `Border-Width/` are groups inside `2. Tokens`,
  sibling to `Color/`, `Scale/`, `Typography/` â€” never their own collection.
- **Both alias `1. Primitives > Scale` exclusively.** Never hardcode a literal FLOAT value into a
  Border-Radius/Border-Width Tier 2 variable except as an explicitly flagged, signed-off exception
  (see the `pill`/`9999` precedent above â€” even that case resolved to a real alias, not a literal).
- **t-shirt naming, not pixel naming.** `none, sm, md, lg, xlg, 2xlg, 3xlg` for radius (plus
  `pill`); `none, sm, md, lg` for width. Do not revert to value-based names (`050`, `100`...) like
  the legacy collection used â€” that's exactly what this skill replaces.
- **`none` is a deliberate addition.** Legacy collections typically don't include a zero step.
  Add it (aliasing `Scale/0`) even when migrating data that didn't have one â€” confirmed standing
  default, not something to ask about each time.
- **5-mode default.** Unless told otherwise, Border-Radius/Border-Width values are identical
  across `Default`, `Lite`, `Priority`, `Privilege`, `Wealth`. Per-brand differentiation is an
  explicit, scoped exception â€” never assumed.
- **Explicit scopes, not `ALL_SCOPES`.** `CORNER_RADIUS` for radius, `STROKE_FLOAT` for width â€”
  even if a legacy collection being migrated used `ALL_SCOPES`.

