## Standing rules (apply throughout all phases)

- `2. Tokens` aliases `1. Primitives > Scale` only for these two groups â€” never a literal value,
  never a non-Scale primitive, except as an explicitly signed-off, documented exception.
- Cross-reference "we already have this" claims against real resolved values, every time.
- Phases 0â€“1 and 4 are read-only. Gate A is a real stop, not a formality.
- Creation order, `resolvedType`, and scopes are effectively permanent at creation time (no
  reorder API; scopes can be edited post-hoc but get them right up front) â€” get them right before
  calling create.
- Never delete a legacy collection without first scanning for live `boundVariables` references
  across the whole document.

